# `package.json` (root and workspace packages)

**Never** edit manifests under **`node_modules`**. Prefer the **repo root** file for app-wide scripts; in **monorepos**, each workspace package follows the same hygiene.

*Aligned with common Node 20+/Next.js App Router repo practices — review quarterly as tooling evolves (as of March 2026).*

## Scripts
- Prefer **clear, scriptable** commands: `dev`, `build`, `start`, `lint`, `typecheck` / `check:types`, `test` — match what **CI** runs so local and pipeline stay aligned.
- Avoid **one-off** `npm run build` in docs when the team standard is **`vercel build`** (see global `best-practices-2026.mdc`)—document the canonical production check.

## Engines and package manager
- Set **`engines.node`** to the **LTS range** the team supports (e.g. `>=20`) to reduce “works on my machine” drift.
- If the repo standardizes on **pnpm/yarn**, consider **`packageManager`** (Corepack) + **lockfile** committed—don’t mix lockfiles.

## Dependencies
- **Pin major** framework deps (`next`, `react`, `typescript`) intentionally; upgrade on a schedule, not ad hoc in unrelated PRs.
- Run **`npm audit`** / platform alerts; don’t silence **security** issues without a ticket and timeline.

## Hygiene
- Use **`private: true`** for apps that are not npm packages.
- Keep **`name` / `version`** sensible if publishing; otherwise version is mainly for internal tagging.

## Monorepos
- Align **shared** dependency versions across workspace packages where they depend on the same libraries; avoid incompatible duplicate majors.
